Step 5.3: Security Best Practices Checklist
Key security practices to implement:

Use specific image versions instead of latest tag
Run containers as non-root users whenever possible
Minimize installed packages to reduce attack surface
Use multi-stage builds to exclude build tools from final image
Scan images regularly in CI/CD pipeline
Keep base images updated with security patches
Use minimal base images like Alpine or Distroless
Set resource limits to prevent DoS attacks
Enable Docker Content Trust for image signing
Implement network segmentation with custom networks
